title: Senior Software Developer job - Peak Power Inc - Toronto, ON | Indeed.com
summary:
Company Background
Innovative start up company that is focused on the fastest growing market segment in the energy industry today – microgrids. With offices in both Toronto and New York, the company is capitalizing on one of the most disruptive periods of change that the 130-year-old electricity system has ever faced- the shift from a centralized utility business model to a decentralized model. As new decentralized technologies such as energy storage, solar and advanced building automation solutions are quickly emerging, the company is developing an innovative software platform to target the most expensive hours of demand and consumption for both building owners and utilities.

Key Responsibilities:

  • Support management, direction, and vision to the Company’s microgrid control software that will incorporate modules developed in-house as well as modules outsourced to a software development company.
  • Project management of software engineers and/or development employees including offshore contractors/consultants to support, run, and change activities in the software development life cycle.
  • Writing advanced complex code for computer systems and serve as a senior source of expertise
  • Review technical standards/specifications, and ensure enterprise and architectural standards and processes are followed.
  • Manage system and user acceptance testing cycles to ensure accurate and quality business solutions.
  • Participate in development and evolution of architecture.
  • Provide design input across a product.
  • Develop software user interface.
  • Ensure integration of the software with necessary hardware electrical components.
  • Identify risks and road blocks to the successful completion of the project and work with management to resolve
  • Manage software development budget and timelines

Qualifications

  • 5+ years of experience in a leadership role in Software / IT projects
  • Experience in the following programing languages is preferred: Java / C / C++ / .net / Python / R / PHP languages and their associated high concurrency, multithreading structure development; able to apply mainstream design approaches to build, architect and optimize such systems for larger user base
  • Experience with Tomcat, apache, nginx, LVS, ActiveMQ and etc, and have past successful application in business cases
  • Experience in developing intelligent systems controls for electronic systems
  • Expertise in database technology (Oracle, DB2, MySQL, PostgreSQL, NoSQL DB and etc), data modeling, design and manipulation, optimization, testing, best practices, tuning, and leading industry trend knowledge
  • Experience with microgrids, renewable energy, distributed generation, and/or energy storage systems preferred
  • Experience with machine learning, IoT, data mining, and/or statistical learning
  • College diploma or University degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or other related fields

Job Location:

  • Toronto, ON
